# Fohlioo — Cursor Project Rules
# Complete project context for AI-assisted development
# Place this file at the root of every Fohlioo repository

---

## WHAT THIS PROJECT IS

Fohlioo is a two-sided AI fashion intelligence platform with three components:

1. **Chrome browser extension** (Manifest V3, TypeScript) — captures real cross-brand shopper behaviour passively as shoppers browse fashion sites
2. **Web app** (React + TypeScript + Tailwind + Vite) — shopper intelligence home: curated feed, style profile, wardrobe, budget tracker
3. **Brand portal** (same web app, separate route) — analytics dashboard for fashion brands: buyer segments, demand forecasting, campaign analytics, pricing intelligence

The extension is the data engine. Without it, neither the shopper product nor the brand intelligence portal has anything to work with. It is the most critical component to build correctly.

**Slogan:** Better choices. Smarter collections.
**Domain:** fohlioo.com
**Contact:** hello@fohlioo.co

---

## THE CORE PRODUCT THESIS

The browser extension captures what shoppers actually do across every fashion site they visit — Cos, Net-a-Porter, Toteme, Zara, ASOS, H&M, etc. This cross-brand behavioural data is converted into two things simultaneously:

- **For shoppers:** a personalised style profile, wardrobe gap detection, budget intelligence, regret detection, curated feed
- **For brands:** buyer segment intelligence, demand forecasting, campaign analytics, pricing intelligence

No direct competitor captures cross-brand shopper behaviour at this level. Phia (phia.com) does price comparison — that is a different problem. WGSN, EDITED, Heuritech are B2B only with no consumer product. Fohlioo is structurally new.

---

## TECH STACK — USE EXACTLY THESE

### Extension
- **Framework:** Plasmo (docs.plasmo.com) — React + TypeScript wrapper for Chrome extensions
- **Language:** TypeScript throughout — no plain JavaScript files
- **Manifest:** V3 only — never use MV2 patterns
- **Storage:** chrome.storage.local for session state, never localStorage

### Web App + Brand Portal
- **Framework:** React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS — utility classes only, no inline styles, no CSS modules
- **Routing:** React Router v6
- **State:** Zustand for global state, React Query (TanStack Query) for server state
- **Deployment:** Vercel

### Backend API
- **Runtime:** Node.js
- **Framework:** Hono — lightweight, edge-compatible, not Express
- **Deployment:** Railway
- **Language:** TypeScript

### Database
- **Primary:** Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- **Vector search:** pgvector — already enabled in Supabase, used for style matching
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth
- **Real-time:** Supabase Realtime for live portal updates

### AI / ML
- **Embeddings:** OpenAI text-embedding-3-small — for product and style matching
- **Fast LLM tasks:** Claude Haiku — search intent, regret detection
- **Deep LLM tasks:** Claude Sonnet — brand insights, complex analysis
- **Segmentation (Phase 1):** Rule-based threshold engine — NO ML models yet
- **Segmentation (Phase 2):** K-means clustering on 30+ event profiles

### Product Catalogue
- **Source:** AWIN affiliate feed — 200+ fashion brands, structured product data
- **Why:** Legal product data with affiliate revenue from day one

### Analytics
- **Tool:** PostHog — product analytics, feature flags, session replay

