## FASHION SITES — KNOWN DATA CHARACTERISTICS

Sites confirmed to have clean JSON-LD (test first):
- cos.com — clean Product JSON-LD
- net-a-porter.com — clean Product JSON-LD
- asos.com — React SPA, has JSON-LD but needs SPA handling
- toteme-studio.com — clean JSON-LD
- arket.com — clean JSON-LD

Sites with partial or no JSON-LD (need DOM fallback):
- zara.com — React SPA, limited JSON-LD, needs DOM scraping
- stories.com — minimal structured data
- hm.com — some JSON-LD but inconsistent

DOM fallback selectors to research per site when JSON-LD is absent:
- Product name: `h1`, `[data-product-name]`, `.product-title`
- Price: `[data-price]`, `.product-price`, `[itemprop="price"]`
- Brand: `[data-brand]`, `.product-brand`, `[itemprop="brand"]`

---

## WHAT NOT TO DO

- Do not use Express — use Hono
- Do not use any MV2 patterns in the extension
- Do not use localStorage in the extension — use chrome.storage.local
- Do not make API calls directly from content scripts — use background.ts as intermediary
- Do not build ML models in Phase 1 — rule-based segmentation only
- Do not add visual components to the extension popup in Phase 1 — focus on data capture
- Do not capture data on non-fashion sites — respect the match list
- Do not intercept Gmail or any non-fashion network requests
- Do not use CSS frameworks in content scripts — style leakage into host page
- Do not store shopper data in plain text — always go through Supabase RLS
- Do not build the web app before the extension data pipeline is working

---

## NOTES FOR CURSOR

When generating code for this project:
- Always use the exact tech stack listed above — never suggest alternatives unprompted
- The extension is built with Plasmo — always follow Plasmo patterns, not raw Chrome extension patterns
- Always generate TypeScript with strict typing
- Database queries always go through the Supabase client — never raw SQL from the frontend
- The segmentation engine is server-side only — never run it in the extension
- Tailwind classes only for styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- When building API endpoints, always validate the request body before touching the database
- All extension-to-background communication uses chrome.runtime.sendMessage with typed message objects

When asked to build a new feature, always ask: does this require visual design? If yes, flag it as blocked pending designer handover. If no, build it.
